Job Description:
The role
At Olam Cocoa, we have a vacancy for a Cocoa Quality Technologist based at our manufacturing facility in Koog aan de Zaan, the Netherlands. In this role, you will be responsible for providing support in quality and regulatory area for the cocoa business, globally. Your passion for identifying opportunities for improvement, executing deep data dives and finding creative solutions is key to deliver trusted and high-quality products to our customers.
Reporting into the European Quality Manager the scope is to support all cocoa sites across the globe, related to quality and regulatory topics. This includes Olam Cocoa BV (Koog aan de Zaan and Wormer), Mannheim, Goole, Valencia, Singapore, BT Cocoa, Ilheus, Bolingbrook, Kumasi, Abidjan and San Pedro.
The jobholder will be responsible for providing support in quality and regulatory area through statistical evaluation, troubleshooting and via projects for the cocoa business. This is obtained by an empiric and curious attitude, pro-active involvement with stakeholders from individual production locations and stakeholders from other departments.
Key deliverables
Proactive initiation and coordination of investigations in relation to changing regulations or ad hoc quality / food safety related challenges. Drives the investigations autonomous. Investigations can be the following:
Statistical evaluation and interpretation of data
Literature research and interpretation
Practical investigation including coordination of sampling and analyses with own or 3rd party laboratories
Leading exploratory projects and/ or participating in these projects
Provide a quarterly statistical review on monitoring data for the cocoa group and the individual production locations against ML’s and MRL’s. Review is used as input to anticipate and manage risk on contaminants, heavy metals and specific legal requirements.
Facilitate data transfer to ECA JRL.
Active participation in programs for instance MOSH/MOAH, %Shell content, Pesticides/Contaminants/Mycotoxins/Allergens.
Provide expert opinion based on statistical evaluation of internal and external ring trials on cocoa products/ cocoa beans and microbiology
Develop, define and evaluate quality performance KPI’s with the production locations (for instance Right First Time, CAPA).

Qualifications and experience
Master/ bachelor’s degree in food science/ nutrition or food science/technology;
• Specialization in statics; • Minimum of 2 years’ experience in a quality role in manufacturing of food/ingredients;
Sound knowledge and proven experience in working with statistical programs (e.g. SPSS/ Statgraphics);
Proven experience working with Excell/ SAP/ LIMS;
Proven experience in project management;
International experience in collaboration with cross-functionals teams and remote collaboration;
Proficient English language skills, verbal and written.
Skills & Competences
Is self-motivated and works autonomous;
Loves to work with lots of data;
Strong written & verbal communication skills;
Creative thinker and empiric mindset;
Ability to work within cross-functional teams and different production locations;
Having a positive and can-do mind set;
Good communication and presentation skills and clear communication, written and verbal.
Are you the Cocoa Quality Technologist we are looking for?
